nodes.documentation:
Library that implements a linked-list queue (FIFO) of bytes32 elements. 
Terminology taken from: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Queue.html#add-E-
nodes.name: LinkedListQueue

nodes.documentation: Adding an element to the tail of the queue
nodes.name: add

nodes.documentation: Return and remove an element from the head of the queue
nodes.name: poll

nodes.documentation: Inserts an element at the head
nodes.name: insertAtHead

nodes.documentation: Gets the head of the list, without removing the element
nodes.name: peek

nodes.documentation: Gets the tail of the list, without removing the element
nodes.name: peekLast

nodes.documentation: Gets the element after the passed element, without removing the element
nodes.name: peekAfter

nodes.documentation:
Due to gas-reasons, count management is not there, it's also not necessary. 
So getting the count is going to be expensive. Better to maintain it at the caller
nodes.name: getCount

nodes.documentation: Clear the head and the tail of the queue. Like erasing the queue
nodes.name: clear
